<item>
            <title>[LU-13461] LNet routing: wrong gw ni may be selected to reach undiscovered peer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13461</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Test scenario is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PeerA: two networks, one interface per network (A1@tcp, A2@tcp1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PeerB: one network, two interfaces (B1@tcp2, B2@tcp2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GW1: two interfaces on peerA&apos;s first net, two facing peerB (R1@tcp, R2@tcp, R3@tcp2, R4@tcp2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GW2: two interfaces on peerA&apos;s second net, two facing peerB (R1@tcp1, R2@tcp1, R3@tcp2, R4@tcp2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Routes on peer A: reach tcp2 via GW1, reach tcp2 via GW2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Routes on peer B: reach tcp via GW1, reach tcp1 via GW2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do not run discovery on peer A from peer B or vice versa.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;Once everything is configured, the following ping may fail from peer A to peer B:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lnetctl ping B1@tcp2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It looks like wrong gateway NI may be selected by peer A:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(lib-move.c:1921:lnet_handle_send()) TRACE: 192.168.122.103@tcp(192.168.122.103@tcp:&amp;lt;?&amp;gt;) -&amp;gt; 192.168.122.110@tcp2(192.168.122.110@tcp2:192.168.122.150@tcp1) &amp;lt;?&amp;gt; : GET try# 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
